text: {| |} RFA Retainer (A329) was an armament support ship of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary. In 1959, Retainer was used with the missile trials ship for trials of replenishment at sea with the new Seaslug missile. == References == Category:Ships of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary Category:Stores ships of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary Category:1950 ships
